WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Use recommended drivers and licensed car companies.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:12.000
Do a quick visual inspection of the vehicle, it should look clean and well maintained.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.500
The driver should be the only occupant.

00:00:16.500 --> 00:00:20.000
Do the seatbelts, locks and windows work?

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:26.000
If travelling by taxi, check the meter & licence.

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:27.500
Chat to the driver. 

00:00:27.500 --> 00:00:29.500
Confirm they are sober, know the destination, 

00:00:29.500 --> 00:00:31.200
and there are no language issues.

00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:34.000
Sit in the rear and wear your seatbelt. 

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:37.000
This is the safest position in the event of a crash.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:40.500
Keep your valuables in a bag at your feet.

00:00:40.500 --> 00:00:44.000
Don't be distracted and remain observant during your journey.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:49.000
Pay the driver inside the taxi.

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:52.000
Double check you haven't left anything behind.

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:59.000
If you are involved in a road traffic incident, let the driver deal with it.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:01.500
Comply with legal requirements, but wait in a safe place.

00:01:01.500 --> 00:01:07.000
Call your emergency contacts to let them know what has happened.
